1
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:12,730
Ready to meet the legends
of the B.S. Brothers?

2
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:17,740
And here are the legends
of the B.S. Brothers.

3
00:00:25,010 --> 00:00:29,400
The story is about
a tight-knit crew of gamers.

4
00:00:29,470 --> 00:00:30,530
A real tight-knit crew.

5
00:00:30,590 --> 00:00:32,830
It's centered around esports

6
00:00:32,850 --> 00:00:36,270
and is about a group of teens
who are passionate about gaming.

7
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:38,950
And the whole B.S. Brothers crew

8
00:00:38,980 --> 00:00:40,590
consists of P'Three,

9
00:00:40,620 --> 00:00:41,590
P'Preaw,

10
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:42,970
P'Laem,

11
00:00:43,050 --> 00:00:43,700
P'Jack,

12
00:00:43,730 --> 00:00:45,060
and P'Toobtub.

13
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:46,820
And of course, Soh.

14
00:00:47,940 --> 00:00:51,850
And the leader of the crew
is a guy named P'Three.

15
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:53,030
Well, let me hear it, then.

16
00:00:53,170 --> 00:00:53,770
Uh...

17
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:54,890
Wait...

18
00:00:56,770 --> 00:00:57,480
Shit,

19
00:00:57,890 --> 00:00:58,690
that was cute.

20
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:01,010
Their dream is to be champions,

21
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:03,800
but they feel like something is missing.

22
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:05,160
Until one day,

23
00:01:05,380 --> 00:01:08,220
there was this tournament
they really wanted to enter.

24
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,520
They thought, "This is it.
We're gonna be the champs."

25
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:21,480
But then, one of them
had to leave the team,

26
00:01:21,510 --> 00:01:22,720
so they were short-handed.

27
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:25,430
The root of all this chaos
is actually P'Toobtub.

28
00:01:25,890 --> 00:01:29,390
He used to be part of our team, right?

29
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:33,120
Then suddenly, he announced
he was quitting the game.

30
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:33,940
- What?
- What?

31
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:35,190
- You'll withdraw?
- You'll withdraw?

32
00:01:35,210 --> 00:01:38,290
Because he has a family now.

33
00:01:38,310 --> 00:01:40,730
So we lost our Support player.

34
00:01:41,370 --> 00:01:42,170
- What?
- What?

35
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:43,690
- With four kids?
- With four kids?

36
00:01:44,380 --> 00:01:47,620
But P'Three already had someone in mind

37
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:51,850
because they'd played together,
and he felt like, "This is the one."

38
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:53,560
This kid has some serious skills.

39
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:55,740
I've got to get him to join the team.

40
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,250
Before we get to that,

41
00:01:59,650 --> 00:02:01,150
can you take off that bear head first?

42
00:02:05,070 --> 00:02:06,910
That's where the story kicks off.

43
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,340
And from then on,
once this kid joins the team,

44
00:02:11,370 --> 00:02:14,880
he has to deal with all kinds of people
and gaming drama.

45
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:18,050
Then all sorts of problems
start to arise.

46
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:20,480
There's the theme of friendship.

47
00:02:20,510 --> 00:02:22,700
Long-time friends suddenly
have to compete against each other.

48
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,510
There's the romance aspect.

49
00:02:24,550 --> 00:02:27,610
There's the drive to win,
the refusal to accept defeat,

50
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:30,040
and so many cool elements
in the show.

51
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,580
You just have to watch it.
Seriously, watch it.

52
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,780
I won't say anything else
because I don't know any.

53
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:37,970
I should mention that
my bruises just finally healed.

54
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,640
I had bruises on my knees and arms.

55
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:44,530
I had to get pretty dirty.

56
00:02:45,550 --> 00:02:47,180
He had some action scenes with Soh.

57
00:02:47,260 --> 00:02:48,060
- Oops.
- Oh...

58
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:51,620
If you're interested in esports,

59
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:55,110
or even if you don't know much
about it, give it a watch.

60
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:56,840
B.S. ...

61
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:57,920
- Brothers.
- Brothers.

62
00:02:57,940 --> 00:02:58,560
B.S. ...

63
00:02:58,570 --> 00:03:02,150
A lot of people probably wonder
why we were born.

64
00:03:02,270 --> 00:03:04,600
Some say it's to find happiness.

65
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:07,590
Others say it's to find
the meaning of life.

66
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:08,730
But as for me...

67
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,280
I was born to...

68
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:11,110
win!

69
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,870
Hello, I'm Maxky, Ratchata Pichetshote.

70
00:03:13,890 --> 00:03:16,080
I play the role of 'Thr33Gamer.'

71
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:20,260
You're so dead,

72
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,220
you damn bear.

73
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:23,040
P'Three has this vibe of being...

74
00:03:23,210 --> 00:03:23,970
handsome.

75
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:25,590
Yeah, exactly.

76
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:26,740
He's a bit cringe.

77
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:28,330
You can tell he's handsome
just by looking at him.

78
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,810
He's what you'd call a show-off,
always acting cool.

79
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,870
He's cheerful and always brings
positive energy to his friends.

80
00:03:34,230 --> 00:03:36,250
But when it's time to get serious,
he really goes for it.

81
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:39,000
I think Three is someone
you just can't rein in.

82
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:40,340
Just let him be.

83
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,530
Yeah, it's better
to just let him do his thing.

84
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:43,550
Yeah, 'cause Jack believes in him.

85
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:45,160
He trusts Three's instincts.

86
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:49,620
Three has a sense
for what should or shouldn't be done.

87
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:51,320
Things like, "I want to do this,"
and so on.

88
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:54,530
Then he'll ask
the rest of the team for help,

89
00:03:54,550 --> 00:03:57,030
and they are always ready
to support him.

90
00:03:57,630 --> 00:04:00,150
Three's the backbone of the team.

91
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:04,770
You know, he's the driving force
behind everything

92
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:08,390
from forming the team
to entering all competitions.

93
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:11,750
He's also the emotional anchor
of the team.

94
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:12,890
On the days the team feels discouraged,

95
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:16,360
on the days Soh feels uneasy,

96
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,000
Three is always
the first one to stand up

97
00:04:19,020 --> 00:04:20,250
and give everyone a boost.

98
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,400
Hi, I'm Bas, Hatsanat,

99
00:04:22,430 --> 00:04:24,030
and I play the role of 'Soh.'

100
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,860
From my perspective,

101
00:04:27,890 --> 00:04:30,760
when Soh is in front of a lot of people,

102
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:32,400
he's an introvert.

103
00:04:33,330 --> 00:04:35,240
He doesn't talk much. He's very shy,

104
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:39,700
quiet, cute, very blunt, and honest.

105
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:42,860
If someone asks him to do something...
Like, if P'Three says,

106
00:04:43,130 --> 00:04:45,330
Why don't you try being in love?
Soh would just go and fall in love.

107
00:04:46,030 --> 00:04:47,470
- He'd just do it?
- Totally.

108
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:50,150
And... don't you wanna date someone?

109
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:53,120
Soh, there's a new movie out tomorrow.

110
00:04:53,350 --> 00:04:54,510
Will you go see it with me?

111
00:04:55,830 --> 00:04:57,260
Sorry, P'Three.

112
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,400
I just want to go on a date with Soh.

113
00:05:00,970 --> 00:05:01,590
Whoa.

114
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:04,910
And actually, Soh has...

115
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:07,220
something buried deep in his heart.

116
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:09,820
If you want to find out,

117
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,140
watch the series.

118
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:14,600
Hi, I'm Jeng, Chotipat.

119
00:05:14,630 --> 00:05:17,290
In 'Be My Player Two,'
I play the role of 'Laem.'

120
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:19,820
Most people call him 'Cher.'

121
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:23,740
Wait. I play Cher,
but most people call him Laem. Yeah.

122
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:25,150
Right.

123
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,360
Laem means sharp. It's his sharp nose.

124
00:05:26,370 --> 00:05:28,180
- Oh.
- That's the nickname. Right.

125
00:05:28,210 --> 00:05:30,860
He's a chatterbox.
He just keeps talking.

126
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,660
He's the type who...

127
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:35,330
His words come out
before his brain can process them.

128
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:40,300
He doesn't have much of a filter
and has overflowing energy.

129
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,110
He loves his friends dearly,

130
00:05:42,130 --> 00:05:45,390
and he's always there,
anytime, anywhere.

131
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,820
Hi, I'm Gunner.

132
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,130
Just a second.

133
00:05:51,930 --> 00:05:54,900
I play the role of 'Jack,' aka JJack.

134
00:05:55,170 --> 00:05:56,700
It's his personality.

135
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:00,250
I feel like Jack is a very quiet person.

136
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:03,070
He has pretty high walls up.

137
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:05,760
That's also reflected
in the way he dresses.

138
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:10,690
Hi, I'm Mean, Wichayaporn.

139
00:06:10,710 --> 00:06:14,890
I play 'Preaw,' aka PreawPreaw
in 'Be My Player Two.'

140
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:18,940
Preaw's character has this vibe of...

141
00:06:18,970 --> 00:06:22,600
She's just an ordinary girl
who likes gaming.

142
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:25,100
And she happens to end up
playing with this crew.

143
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:26,720
She's a bit of a tomboy.

144
00:06:26,930 --> 00:06:29,020
She's got a bit of a boyish side,
but not overly so.

145
00:06:29,050 --> 00:06:33,560
She still has that girly side,
being cute and all.

146
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:38,020
Hi, I'm Newton, Waiyakorn,
playing the role of 'Ten.'

147
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:40,940
Ten's personality?

148
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,540
He's not much of a talker.

149
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:45,180
Just like me, actually.

150
00:06:45,210 --> 00:06:48,970
He doesn't really speak
his feelings out loud.

151
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:52,460
He bottles up all those
little frustrations and slights.

152
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,700
The Ten we see today...

153
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:58,540
He doesn't just suddenly
become selfish and leave.

154
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:01,170
But there were many underlying issues,

155
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:03,800
like his own feelings
of being underappreciated

156
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:07,500
regarding his experiences with friends
that built up over time.

157
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:10,900
And when it finally exploded, he just...

158
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:13,600
parted ways with his friends
and joined another team.

159
00:07:13,870 --> 00:07:18,170
You could say Ten
is a major turning point in the story

160
00:07:18,190 --> 00:07:20,580
because after Ten left,

161
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:23,940
he took what he learned
from the previous team

162
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,770
and used it
to give the other team an advantage.

163
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,800
That's why he's holding the upper hand.

164
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:34,480
From what I gathered initially,

165
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:37,940
I thought P'Three must be
just like me in my YouTube videos,

166
00:07:37,970 --> 00:07:41,440
or Zellfie,
with that high-octane energy.

167
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:44,270
Just saying whatever he wants
and doing whatever he pleases.

168
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:46,380
But once I learned more about him,

169
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,120
spent some time with this character,

170
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:50,870
and did all the workshops,

171
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:54,650
I realized we are actually
nothing alike.

172
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,260
I thought he was like Zellfie.

173
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:58,260
No, he's even more
over-the-top than that.

174
00:07:58,380 --> 00:08:03,890
Zellfie might be crazy,
but he doesn't show it as much.

175
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:06,150
Right, but P'Three is just extra
in every way.

176
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:08,910
He's goofy, cringe, and handsome.

177
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:10,340
Maxed out in every way.

178
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:11,990
Actually, I'm an extrovert.

179
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:16,320
I like talking to people,
playing around, and having fun.

180
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,790
Soh, on the other hand, is an introvert.

181
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:18,960
We're completely different.

182
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,950
Like night and day, total opposites.

183
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:26,030
Very. He's extremely shy.

184
00:08:26,060 --> 00:08:27,810
That's just his character, you know.

185
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,590
A shy, quiet person.

186
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:32,840
But he fits in well
with the team, right?

187
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:35,800
He does, thanks to P'Three.

188
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,190
- Oh, it's P'Three.
- Exactly.

189
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:40,610
He is always there to encourage Soh,
no matter what happens.

190
00:08:42,470 --> 00:08:45,550
Honestly, we started this
right after our previous series,

191
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:48,470
- Yeah.
- and the roles are completely...

192
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:50,000
different for both of us.

193
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:50,800
- That's right.
- His role...

194
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,940
My previous role was 'Johan,'

195
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:55,080
- who was quiet, calm, and cool.
- Very stoic.

196
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:57,140
While 'North' was like...

197
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,980
- In this series, it's the opposite.
- Totally.

198
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,110
- Whoa.
- Now you're P'Three.

199
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:02,510
P'Three is so over-the-top,

200
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:03,870
while Soh is more like...

201
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,900
- "Yes, sir. Yes, sir."
- "Sure, P'Three. You're so good."

202
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:08,270
Sweet and polite.

203
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,040
- "You're amazing, P'Three."
- Yeah, exactly.

204
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:11,750
Like, innocent and all that.

205
00:09:11,790 --> 00:09:13,590
Yeah, it's new for both of us.

206
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:14,520
- Totally
- Yeah.

207
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:16,380
I feel like
we're actually quite similar.

208
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,370
Let me give you some background first.

209
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:21,180
They said the perfect cast for Cher
was almost impossible to find

210
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:23,700
because he has
a massive amount of energy,

211
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,790
even more than the lead, P'Three.

212
00:09:26,810 --> 00:09:30,010
During the casting,
they showed me a video of someone.

213
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,510
It was a YouTube video of Maxky.
Guess what he was shouting.

214
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:34,680
So damn handsome.

215
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:37,680
And I thought,
"Crap, how am I going to pull this off?"

216
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:42,000
Eventually, I got the role,
and I feel like...

217
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,330
I'm really happy I got this role,

218
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:49,280
and it fits my current personality
quite well, too.

219
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:51,210
I don't think
there's anyone in this world

220
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:53,730
who shouts
every single sentence they say.

221
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,030
If you meet Laem

222
00:09:55,050 --> 00:09:57,450
and really get to know him,

223
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,940
you'll either end up loving him

224
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:01,890
or find him annoying because...

225
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:05,290
every scene he's in starts with
him shouting, "Hey, P'Three!"

226
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:08,100
Like, who would be crazy enough
to shout all the time, right?

227
00:10:08,330 --> 00:10:10,870
But Laem is a character
with truly overflowing energy.

228
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,290
If my energy is at this level,

229
00:10:12,310 --> 00:10:14,260
on set, my energy has to be...

230
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:17,650
like four or five times higher,
maybe ten times higher.

231
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:18,590
So I feel like...

232
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,670
it's exhausting.

233
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:23,020
It's really fun, though.

234
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:26,250
There are both
similarities and differences.

235
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:29,230
But only a few differences.
We're similar in terms of...

236
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:33,070
being tough. We hang out with guys
without feeling out of place.

237
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,940
However, for Preaw,

238
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:37,230
she's better than me
in that she's very open-minded,

239
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:41,480
and she's probably
a better gamer than I am.

240
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:47,500
I'm not exactly the most focused person.

241
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:51,280
- Did you mean your role?
- No, I mean myself, Gunner.

242
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:52,570
I'm not that focused.

243
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:55,020
We're not alike at all.
We're worlds apart.

244
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:56,350
Jack's very mature.

245
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:59,620
He's the most mature one
in B.S. Brothers.

246
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:03,070
Jack is the type
who thinks before he speaks.

247
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,770
Whenever he says something,

248
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:07,750
he takes full responsibility
for his words.

249
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:09,940
But Ten is the kind of person who...

250
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:13,900
just says whatever he wants.
If he wants to hurt someone's feelings,

251
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:15,200
he just does it.

252
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:18,330
I'd say we're about 40% alike.

253
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:20,000
40% in the sense that...

254
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:23,240
we tend to keep problems to ourselves.

255
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:25,790
I might speak up eventually,
just not right away,

256
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,720
but Ten doesn't speak at all.

257
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:30,150
He bottles everything up
until he explodes,

258
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:33,090
and then he just doesn't care anymore.

259
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,040
Personally, I'm...

260
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:39,010
I'd say I'm not as hot-headed as Ten.

261
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,000
I think every role is a challenge,

262
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,750
especially the part where...

263
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:45,670
Jack barely speaks.

264
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:49,000
So his eyes, gestures,
and body language...

265
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:51,830
need to show what he's thinking

266
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:54,800
before he speaks anything.

267
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,810
Like I said, Ten doesn't really talk.

268
00:11:57,900 --> 00:12:02,500
So, how do you make people
feel the suffocating emotions

269
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:06,340
and burning pain inside him?

270
00:12:06,370 --> 00:12:09,900
Another challenge was the hair color.

271
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,400
Because...

272
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:15,950
by the time we finished filming,
I was practically going bald.

273
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,090
I had to touch up my roots
every two weeks.

274
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:19,640
I'm really dedicated, you know.

275
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:23,150
I put my hair on the line for this.

276
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:26,200
I wasn't even going to take this role

277
00:12:26,230 --> 00:12:27,950
because I was supposed to go abroad.

278
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,530
I was going on
an exchange program to Spain.

279
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:33,530
So I had to choose between
taking on this series or going to Spain.

280
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:35,370
I told my dad
I wanted to be in this series

281
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,680
because it seemed really interesting.

282
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:41,220
You know, the first role
that I'd really get to be myself.

283
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:45,980
Usually, I'm playing villains
or characters who pick on others.

284
00:12:46,010 --> 00:12:49,020
But this time, I get to play
someone full of energy.

285
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,420
I'm a fun character,
the kind that everyone will love.

286
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,490
I really wanted to do it,

287
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:55,770
so I told my dad I wouldn't go abroad
and would do this instead.

288
00:12:55,910 --> 00:12:58,520
That's how I ended up with this role.

289
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:01,070
I was initially cast as Ten,

290
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,980
and I thought the character
was really fascinating

291
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:06,580
because of his depth.
He's not the type to...

292
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:09,770
Like I mentioned,
he keeps his feelings bottled up inside

293
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:13,030
which means he's a man of few words.

294
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:14,570
He speaks little but feels a lot,

295
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:17,400
so I had to convey as much as possible
through my facial expressions.

296
00:13:17,690 --> 00:13:20,890
In the series I've worked on before,

297
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:24,550
there hasn't been one that focused on
working together as a team.

298
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:27,850
Most of them
were solely about the main couple,

299
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:31,170
and the plots were
primarily focused on their stories.

300
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:34,370
This series also focuses on
a group dynamic.

301
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,820
Plus, WeTV...

302
00:13:35,850 --> 00:13:38,520
put a lot of emphasis
on the B.S. Brothers crew,

303
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:43,970
so I felt like I wanted to be
a part of this group.

304
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:47,420
The real reason
I took this role, honestly,

305
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:48,950
was because Maxky's name was on it.

306
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:51,270
Yeah, because of him.

307
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:54,420
I'd actually worked with him
on a previous project,

308
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:56,150
so when they reached out to me

309
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,630
and told me Maxky was in this, too,

310
00:13:57,660 --> 00:14:00,280
I felt like, "Okay, this is
going to be a breeze."

311
00:14:00,470 --> 00:14:03,680
You know, 'cause I'd have at least
one friend on set with me,

312
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:06,620
and I wouldn't be so awkward or shy.

313
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:09,400
It'd be easy to work together,
so I accepted the role.

314
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:12,270
- P'Preaw?
- P'Preaw or Mean...

315
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:15,770
- Mean, yeah.
- We've worked together before.

316
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:18,150
Yeah, so we were already somewhat close.

317
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:20,900
Then she talked to him,
and they realized...

318
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:23,370
- We have similar interests.
- Very similar.

319
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:25,750
- About...
- I'd finish shooting five scenes,

320
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,100
and they'd still be talking
about the same thing.

321
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:28,840
- For over an hour.
- I was so confused.

322
00:14:28,860 --> 00:14:30,600
- Way more than an hour.
- Seriously, like...

323
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:31,430
The whole day.

324
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:33,630
I'd finish shooting
and see them sitting there talking.

325
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:35,050
So I'd go out to shoot,
finish, and come back.

326
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:36,130
- Still there.
- Still there.

327
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,510
I'd go out to shoot more scenes
and come back.

328
00:14:37,570 --> 00:14:38,520
They'd still be at it.

329
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:40,790
- Still the same topic.
- Even when I came back after lunch,

330
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:42,310
they weren't done talking.

331
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:44,240
- And it was just one topic.
- Yeah, just one.

332
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:46,340
- They have the same interests.
- Right, exactly.

333
00:14:46,620 --> 00:14:49,030
Both of them...
The three of us, actually,

334
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:51,180
share very similar interests.

335
00:14:51,210 --> 00:14:53,820
It's all about songs,
music, and records.

336
00:14:53,850 --> 00:14:55,350
Vinyl records, yeah.

337
00:14:55,370 --> 00:14:56,680
Bas is a collector.

338
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,410
I even sneaked over to his house.

339
00:14:58,450 --> 00:15:00,740
He showed me
his entire vinyl collection.

340
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,880
Whoa, it was magnificent.

341
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,050
He literally told me,

342
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,790
Jeng, just tell me
which record you want.

343
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:09,880
I'd name a band,
and he'd go digging and pull it out.

344
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:12,550
He remembers everything,
and he has them all.

345
00:15:12,830 --> 00:15:15,240
Same for Mean,
she has a ton of vinyls, too.

346
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:18,700
So when we talk about this stuff,
it never stops.

347
00:15:18,730 --> 00:15:21,960
He collects so many vinyls
that I was so shocked.

348
00:15:22,110 --> 00:15:23,520
"Bas, do you have this one?"
He said, "I do."

349
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:24,960
"Do you have this one?"
He said, "I do."

350
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:26,780
"I have this one, too."
And I was like...

351
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,030
Just tell me every record you have.

352
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:31,920
We were basically
recommending vinyl to each other.

353
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:34,000
P'Three, don't be jealous.

354
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:43,960
Was her back made of steel or what?
It was hard as hell.

355
00:15:45,810 --> 00:15:47,260
Just like I thought.

356
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,660
Maxky is a funny guy.

357
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:50,070
He is just...

358
00:15:50,100 --> 00:15:52,760
Maxky, Bas, Jeng...
Everyone, actually,

359
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:55,100
made the vibe on set so relaxed

360
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,800
and very fun.

361
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,020
How was it on set?

362
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,800
- It was fun.
- So much fun.

363
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:00,460
Because we...

364
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:02,870
Honestly, we were familiar
with many of the people.

365
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:03,780
- The crew, too.
- And then...

366
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,100
the others might have been new,

367
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:08,300
- Yeah.
- But we clicked after some fights.

368
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,730
- "Some fights."
- Some fights?

369
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,570
- Yeah, to get closer.
- Whoa.

370
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,850
No, but seriously,

371
00:16:13,950 --> 00:16:15,730
we were quite awkward at first

372
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:17,270
- We were.
- because we...

373
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:19,830
didn't really know them yet.

374
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,760
But it felt like everyone
already knew each other,

375
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:24,690
so we sat down and talked
to break the ice,

376
00:16:24,710 --> 00:16:26,820
- asking about each other's interests.
- Right.

377
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:29,120
Then later on, we just couldn't stop.

378
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:30,650
We found our common interests.

379
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:31,860
- Exactly.
- We had so much to talk about.

380
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:33,750
- Oh, it went on forever.
- Couldn't stop.

381
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:36,960
And personally, I had
such a blast watching this show.

382
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:37,520
Yeah.

383
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:40,130
When everyone acts,
like when you play with Jeng,

384
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,250
wow, it's so much fun.

385
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:44,420
- They'd play, and I'd be there smiling.
- Loved it.

386
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,860
Usually, I'm the active one.

387
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,650
But this time, I just watched.

388
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,370
- Right.
- I was so happy.

389
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,630
- Watching is fun, too.
- Yeah, in the scenes,

390
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,760
- he'd sit in the corner and say,
- Yeah.

391
00:16:54,830 --> 00:16:57,790
- "Hey, you and Jeng, go for it."
- Go for it.

392
00:16:57,810 --> 00:16:59,910
- It was so fun, really.
- "I really enjoy watching you guys."

393
00:16:59,950 --> 00:17:00,740
And I meant it.

394
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,210
Did we prank each other?

395
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:04,330
- No, not that much.
- No pranks.

396
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:06,910
- Yeah, we'd just play around.
- We adore each other.

397
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:08,890
- We all adore each other.
- It was more of a caring vibe.

398
00:17:08,910 --> 00:17:10,550
Say, if Bas started singing a song,

399
00:17:10,570 --> 00:17:12,410
whoever knew the song
would join in.

400
00:17:12,430 --> 00:17:14,370
Sometimes, Jeng would sing,

401
00:17:14,390 --> 00:17:16,890
- Jeng, yeah.
- and then Bas's voice would follow,

402
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,280
as if they planned it beforehand.

403
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:22,230
- "Hi, Maxky."
- Right, right.

404
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:25,060
Yeah, and Gunner would be a bit quiet.

405
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:27,400
But he's a very sweet guy.

406
00:17:28,470 --> 00:17:28,850
Exactly.

407
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:31,930
- As for Newton? Well...
- I've known him for a long time.

408
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:33,920
- I've known Newton for ages.
- Yeah, for quite a while.

409
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,730
- Right.
- But this is our first series together.

410
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:39,570
Yeah, he can talk so much, too.

411
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:40,440
Exactly.

412
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:42,430
It was so much fun
spending time with them.

413
00:17:43,470 --> 00:17:45,500
This project was actually
the least difficult one.

414
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:49,050
It has a much bigger cast
than other projects I've done,

415
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:51,720
but it was the easiest one
to adjust to

416
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:54,730
because, like I said,
Maxky has this special way about him.

417
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:58,370
He brings everyone together
even if we've never met before.

418
00:17:58,580 --> 00:18:00,410
And for Mean, she's so lovely.

419
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:03,680
She's sweet
and always looking to help out.

420
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:06,730
She knows a lot of random facts.

421
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,880
She's also really kind
and warm-hearted.

422
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,030
Most importantly,

423
00:18:10,340 --> 00:18:14,190
I always see her bringing snacks
to share with everyone.

424
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,930
I'd say the cast is very funny.

425
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:17,950
How so?

426
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:21,760
Well, with the characters
that Maxky and Bas play,

427
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,310
whenever they're acting,

428
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:25,310
most of the funny bits

429
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:29,290
actually come from
both of them improvising.

430
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:30,420
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

431
00:18:30,450 --> 00:18:32,810
Some of that stuff isn't in the script.

432
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,540
And I laughed.

433
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,510
Look at Mean here.

434
00:18:38,430 --> 00:18:40,990
- I always cracked up.
- Literally. You couldn't hold it.

435
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:42,730
You should check it out for yourselves.

436
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:46,310
If you watch episodes one and two,
you'll see that...

437
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:51,790
there's a certain chemistry
that makes the audience feel like,

438
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,420
"Damn, this is so real."

439
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:58,290
I've done comedies before but never
clicked with anyone this much.

440
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,930
Like with Maxky,
on the first day we met,

441
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:04,550
we talked as if
we'd known each other for a long time.

442
00:19:04,570 --> 00:19:08,530
He has this special something
that just makes us click.

443
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:10,130
We weren't close,
and we have a big age gap.

444
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,650
But once we talked, it felt like
we'd known each other for ages.

445
00:19:12,810 --> 00:19:14,450
I'm still quite green in this field.

446
00:19:14,470 --> 00:19:17,520
I don't have much experience
in the industry,

447
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:20,150
so being on set makes me pretty nervous.

448
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:22,160
Plus, I got to work with...

449
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:24,760
Maxky, Bas, and Gunner.

450
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:29,320
You know, people with
a ton of experience. They're pros.

451
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,970
I put a bit of pressure on myself,

452
00:19:31,990 --> 00:19:33,710
but I tried my best to stay relaxed

453
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:36,120
and talk to them as much as I could.

454
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:39,080
In the end, I found it fun being on set.

455
00:19:39,110 --> 00:19:43,070
And there's this sense of friendship
when we're in a scene together.

456
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:45,030
It was fun,
and we played off each other.

457
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:48,240
Maxky is incredibly talented,
I have to admit,

458
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:52,200
and he helped me out
so many times when I felt...

459
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:53,390
you know, pressured.

460
00:19:53,410 --> 00:19:56,690
I'd get really nervous
and start to panic on set.

461
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:59,550
He'd help me out, saying,
"Hey, take it easy. Calm down."

462
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:02,610
So, thank you so much.
I really appreciate it.

463
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,130
Honestly, I'd like to thank this series,

464
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:08,010
the whole crew, and all the cast.

465
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,460
They brought me back into gaming,

466
00:20:10,540 --> 00:20:14,420
and I'd almost forgotten how fun it is
to play games with friends.

467
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:17,130
That's how it was on set.
It was a blast.

468
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:19,930
- Do I play games?
- Yes.

469
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:23,320
Well, I know my way
around a game or two.

470
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,700
Oh, yes. I do play games.

471
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:27,900
We even played
the first season of this game.

472
00:20:28,010 --> 00:20:29,790
My dad had me playing since I was five.

473
00:20:29,810 --> 00:20:31,230
- Whoa.
- Yeah, I played with my dad.

474
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:33,340
- Oh.
- Ever heard of Battle Realms?

475
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,740
No? Never heard of it, huh?

476
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:39,620
When it comes to gaming,
I don't really have any issues.

477
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:43,240
I'm pretty quick at picking things up.

478
00:20:43,370 --> 00:20:46,580
RoV is actually
one of my favorite games.

479
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:50,460
I've been playing
since the early seasons.

480
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:53,600
I'm a huge fan of soccer games
and everything related to soccer.

481
00:20:53,630 --> 00:20:56,800
- Right, but speaking of RoV,
- Yeah.

482
00:20:56,820 --> 00:21:00,720
since we're in this series,
obviously we all have to play RoV.

483
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:03,170
I'm not just bluffing, though.
Look at this.

484
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:06,490
Whoa, look at that. Alright.

485
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:08,920
So, you can't say I don't play RoV.

486
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:10,110
I do, and I'm a big spender, too.

487
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:14,160
I'm all about skins. Doesn't matter
if I suck as long as I have them.

488
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:15,740
So, yeah. RoV, please...

489
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:18,270
You're welcome to sponsor us again.

490
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:22,810
I played RoV
back when it first came out.

491
00:21:23,580 --> 00:21:27,390
That must have been
almost ten years ago, right around then.

492
00:21:27,410 --> 00:21:30,720
I played it back then,
but once I started university,

493
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,890
I got busy with work and everything,
so I quit.

494
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:38,770
I only came back to it
because I was cast in this series.

495
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:39,850
That's why I had to get back into it.

496
00:21:40,220 --> 00:21:42,010
I used to play it
back in high school,

497
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,570
but I lost so much that...

498
00:21:44,590 --> 00:21:47,230
I ended up just deleting the game.

499
00:21:48,170 --> 00:21:51,280
For one, Preaw is an esports athlete.

500
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,170
She's definitely played more games
than I have.

501
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:56,600
So, the research I had to do...

502
00:21:57,090 --> 00:22:01,150
There were some scenes where I had to
compete in the Pro League.

503
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:03,150
To be in the Pro League,
I had to look up...

504
00:22:03,170 --> 00:22:05,000
to see how...

505
00:22:05,050 --> 00:22:09,300
I'd watch live streams
of actual esports athletes competing.

506
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,520
I'd watch them during a match

507
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:15,870
to see how they reacted
while playing, like...

508
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:18,730
what kind of emotions
they would show.

509
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,690
And I had to work on my gameplay, too.

510
00:22:20,890 --> 00:22:24,250
That was another thing
I had to work on.

511
00:22:25,060 --> 00:22:28,650
I'd set up gaming sessions
with everyone in the team.

512
00:22:28,670 --> 00:22:30,780
- So you had to reinstall it?
- Yeah, I reinstalled it.

513
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,760
I was trying to get you back, RoV.

514
00:22:32,980 --> 00:22:34,660
Once again.

515
00:22:34,690 --> 00:22:37,180
As for the Carry role,
I'd never played it before.

516
00:22:37,550 --> 00:22:39,870
The character I play
in the game is Violet,

517
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,170
and Violet has high mobility,

518
00:22:42,190 --> 00:22:44,160
like she'd roll, shoot, or dodge.

519
00:22:44,190 --> 00:22:46,920
Your hands have to be super active
the whole time.

520
00:22:47,150 --> 00:22:50,790
So playing Carry is something new
and very challenging for me.

521
00:22:50,810 --> 00:22:54,730
I really respect
actual esports athletes

522
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:57,260
who are good at RoV.
They're incredibly skilled.

523
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:58,950
Ten plays as a Carry.

524
00:22:58,970 --> 00:23:00,400
I actually play Carry, too.

525
00:23:00,430 --> 00:23:03,560
I mean, Carry is my main role.

526
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:06,850
It depends on what the team is missing,

527
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,270
but if I could choose, it would be...

528
00:23:08,710 --> 00:23:11,640
Carry, Mage, or a Dark Slayer Laner...

529
00:23:12,030 --> 00:23:13,780
most of the time.
I don't really play as a Jungler

530
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:16,340
'cause it carries too much
of the team's expectations.

531
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:17,960
Or it might end up
being a disaster like P'Three.

532
00:23:18,490 --> 00:23:20,100
In the series, I play as a Jungler.

533
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:23,390
I'm a Jungler, the King of the Jungle.

534
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:27,070
You could say I'm the one
who backs up my teammates.

535
00:23:27,430 --> 00:23:28,930
If they're in trouble,
I have to step in.

536
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:31,220
I'm the playmaker.

537
00:23:31,270 --> 00:23:34,030
Usually, the Support
will initiate the fight,

538
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,680
but I have to close the deal
and finish them off.

539
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:39,920
- I'm super important.
- And is there anyone to back you up?

540
00:23:40,380 --> 00:23:41,360
- Not a soul.
- Oh...

541
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:43,030
Completely alone.

542
00:23:43,050 --> 00:23:44,370
No, I back them up.

543
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,970
They'd initiate a fight.

544
00:23:45,990 --> 00:23:47,800
I'd wait for the right moment,
and then I...

545
00:23:49,090 --> 00:23:50,110
- Boom.
- Perfect.

546
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:51,540
But you're...

547
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:54,310
not that great, are you?
Based on when we played together.

548
00:23:54,550 --> 00:23:58,640
Back when I played,
I preferred Mage and Tank.

549
00:23:59,260 --> 00:24:00,670
Yeah, I played those two roles.

550
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:02,890
I didn't really play Carry
because I felt like...

551
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:06,070
they have to, you know,
dive into the thick of it.

552
00:24:06,090 --> 00:24:08,460
But I'm not the type to dive in.

553
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:11,770
I'm usually a bit of a scaredy-cat.
I don't want to charge in.

554
00:24:11,790 --> 00:24:13,950
And a Carry has to be aggressive
and go for it.

555
00:24:13,970 --> 00:24:16,960
Look, a Carry with zero damage.

556
00:24:17,010 --> 00:24:18,600
How is that even possible?

557
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,710
The first time I played as it,
I thought, "I'm screwed."

558
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:24,530
I have to be a really good female Carry
in the series,

559
00:24:24,550 --> 00:24:26,660
so I had to do
a lot of research for this.

560
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:28,710
A Carry can hide behind their teammates.

561
00:24:28,780 --> 00:24:32,730
Talking big, but then
ducking behind the Tank.

562
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:35,910
Another thing is,
you won't be lonely playing Carry

563
00:24:36,230 --> 00:24:37,870
because there will be
two people in the lane.

564
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:41,930
There's a Support or a Roamer
in the same lane,

565
00:24:41,950 --> 00:24:46,340
so at least you can escape.
They'll protect you.

566
00:24:46,350 --> 00:24:50,530
Or if anything happens,
you can be like, "Help, help."

567
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:51,700
And I have to say...

568
00:24:52,430 --> 00:24:54,360
this is one thing
I have in common with Soh.

569
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:56,140
It's the gaming position.

570
00:24:56,650 --> 00:24:58,680
I'm a Support, just like Soh.

571
00:24:59,250 --> 00:25:00,800
- I also play Support.
- Oh, okay.

572
00:25:00,870 --> 00:25:03,320
I've been a Support
since the game launched.

573
00:25:04,090 --> 00:25:07,460
I feel like it's one of
the most indispensable roles.

574
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:12,970
And if the Support isn't good,
the team can't move forward.

575
00:25:13,370 --> 00:25:15,810
It's an important role,
but everyone tends to overlook it.

576
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:19,310
The Support role is always overlooked,

577
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:22,890
but I think it is
a very important role.

578
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:25,660
For me, Mage, Support, Jungle players

579
00:25:25,710 --> 00:25:29,050
have to constantly move and fight.

580
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:30,670
They have to be
the ones making team fights,

581
00:25:30,710 --> 00:25:34,540
so I see Support
as an indispensable and vital role.

582
00:25:35,650 --> 00:25:36,750
Laem plays as a Mage.

583
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:40,400
He's a Mid Laner who helps
both the side lanes.

584
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:41,650
I can play every role.

585
00:25:41,670 --> 00:25:43,280
I really play every single role,

586
00:25:43,310 --> 00:25:45,120
but I'm definitely best at Support.

587
00:25:45,140 --> 00:25:47,550
No matter what game I'm playing,

588
00:25:47,580 --> 00:25:52,820
I'm the type who learns
how to play every role so that...

589
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:56,850
Well, games usually require
a five-player squad, right?

590
00:25:57,020 --> 00:25:59,290
Sometimes, someone might not show up,

591
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:03,340
so I have to fill in
whatever role is missing.

592
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,480
You've got to be flexible,

593
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:06,020
- I know, right?
- playing multiple roles

594
00:26:06,050 --> 00:26:07,620
or multiple heroes.

595
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:09,370
In the series, I play
as a Dark Slayer Laner.

596
00:26:09,420 --> 00:26:12,090
Back in high school,
I thought playing a Carry was easy.

597
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:13,850
But playing as a Dark Slayer Laner

598
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:16,330
made me feel a lot more connected
to the character

599
00:26:16,580 --> 00:26:18,630
and understand being a lone wolf better.

600
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:21,280
(Which role do you like playing?)

601
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,220
- For real?
- Yeah.

602
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,660
- From the bottom of my heart?
- Deep down inside, yeah.

603
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:26,490
I want to play Mage.

604
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:29,030
I want to play Mage and Carry.

605
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:30,830
You want to play Carry?

606
00:26:31,820 --> 00:26:34,240
Nope. I don't think
you're on my level anyway.

607
00:26:34,620 --> 00:26:36,080
We're just in different leagues.

608
00:26:36,100 --> 00:26:38,390
It's been my role since I was a kid.

609
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:40,390
- It's a bit of a long story.
- Alright, go for it.

610
00:26:40,420 --> 00:26:43,570
So, ever since RoV first launched,

611
00:26:43,830 --> 00:26:45,610
I've been playing since the closed beta

612
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:47,470
back when I first started
my YouTube channel.

613
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:50,780
They let me play in the closed beta,
and I just kept playing.

614
00:26:51,020 --> 00:26:52,520
And I was like, "Man, I love Mages."

615
00:26:52,540 --> 00:26:54,050
At first, you know...

616
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:56,310
Everyone was like, "Hey, play Valhein."

617
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,760
- Yeah, yeah.
- Mm-hm. And?

618
00:26:57,780 --> 00:26:59,520
So I played Valhein, and it was easy.

619
00:26:59,550 --> 00:27:01,840
I just kept shooting.
Nothing special.

620
00:27:01,950 --> 00:27:04,720
Then after a while...
I remember it clearly

621
00:27:04,740 --> 00:27:07,120
that the first Jungler I played
was Nakroth.

622
00:27:07,970 --> 00:27:08,850
A tough one.

623
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,080
I felt like being good at it
would look so cool.

624
00:27:11,110 --> 00:27:12,560
He's...

625
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,340
Yeah, exactly.

626
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:14,620
High mobility heroes are just cool.

627
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,530
Aesthetics over skill.
I don't care if I'm good or not.

628
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:17,750
I've gotta look cool first.

629
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:20,840
Right, so I tried playing Nakroth.

630
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:22,280
Not my style.

631
00:27:22,940 --> 00:27:24,610
- Couldn't pull off the cool factor.
- Better go back to being a Mage.

632
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:25,800
Better stick to Mage and Carry.

633
00:27:25,830 --> 00:27:26,880
So I played Mage and Carry,

634
00:27:26,900 --> 00:27:29,520
but once my friends
started playing together...

635
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,360
This friend was a great Mage.

636
00:27:31,390 --> 00:27:32,390
This one was a pro Carry.

637
00:27:32,410 --> 00:27:33,620
This one was an amazing Support.

638
00:27:33,950 --> 00:27:35,380
I couldn't play as a Dark Slayer Laner.

639
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:37,300
So, a Jungler it is.

640
00:27:38,210 --> 00:27:39,710
- That's all that was left.
- Back to a Jungler.

641
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:40,650
Just a Jungler.

642
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:43,140
It's like the only answer.

643
00:27:43,990 --> 00:27:45,040
- Only one.
- But if you pull it off,

644
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:48,860
- you get to show off.
- And that sentence started with 'if.'

645
00:27:50,430 --> 00:27:52,640
Everyone just blames the Jungler first.

646
00:27:52,740 --> 00:27:54,110
I don't get it at all.

647
00:27:54,170 --> 00:27:57,720
Jungler, why aren't you ganking?
You're too slow. Check the map!

648
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,700
Man, I haven't even finished farming
or got the Sage Buff yet.

649
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:03,470
- Okay.
- Just talking about it pisses me off.

650
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:04,870
Whoa, why is that?

651
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:07,950
In the series, there are moments
where things flow smoothly.

652
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:10,640
You know, easy peasy.
Three's a gamer after all.

653
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:13,330
A famous streamer,
quite skilled himself.

654
00:28:14,050 --> 00:28:16,180
But when emotions get involved

655
00:28:16,380 --> 00:28:19,670
and things start getting heated,
he can get too tilted.

656
00:28:19,810 --> 00:28:23,960
Who do you think is better?
You or him?

657
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:27,390
No one is better than anyone else.

658
00:28:27,510 --> 00:28:29,640
It just depends on the situation

659
00:28:29,660 --> 00:28:30,840
and the role you've been given.

660
00:28:31,340 --> 00:28:35,280
- It's how well you handle it.
- What if it was a 1v1?

661
00:28:35,300 --> 00:28:36,030
We've never done a 1v1.

662
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:37,040
- Never?
- Right.

663
00:28:37,060 --> 00:28:39,990
But in the series,
you're actually better, right?

664
00:28:40,140 --> 00:28:43,230
Soh is probably the better player

665
00:28:43,610 --> 00:28:45,250
'cause he is a total game nerd.

666
00:28:45,770 --> 00:28:47,440
- I see.
- A total game nerd.

667
00:28:47,570 --> 00:28:49,900
Yeah, when he plays,
he looks up data

668
00:28:49,930 --> 00:28:52,100
and is very meticulous
about his gameplay.

669
00:28:52,590 --> 00:28:55,760
I just love playing Valhein.
He's a classic.

670
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,430
One of the OG heroes of the game.

671
00:28:57,460 --> 00:29:00,170
You can gain stacks.

672
00:29:00,190 --> 00:29:04,320
Since his second skill can stun targets,
I feel like...

673
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:07,970
he's a hero that lets you both escape...

674
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:10,420
and engage enemies easily, too.

675
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,970
It feels complete, all-in-one.

676
00:29:13,290 --> 00:29:14,630
And his crit damage is insane.

677
00:29:14,810 --> 00:29:18,340
My favorite heroes change all the time
depending on the skins.

678
00:29:18,370 --> 00:29:21,880
If a new skin is stunning,
then I'll favor that hero.

679
00:29:21,910 --> 00:29:26,250
Right now, I like Tulen
because of the Gojo Satoru skin.

680
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:30,010
Yeah, the blindfold and white hair.
It's so damn cool.

681
00:29:30,170 --> 00:29:31,320
Back then, I liked Errol

682
00:29:31,350 --> 00:29:34,110
because of the One-Punch Man
collaboration skin.

683
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:37,870
Saitama's friend, you know.
I don't remember the name.

684
00:29:38,020 --> 00:29:40,430
So it just changes
depending on the game's updates.

685
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:43,430
Without a skin,
my skills just won't show.

686
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:47,200
- So that's how you reached Conqueror?
- Exactly, because of the skins.

687
00:29:47,970 --> 00:29:48,840
That's a fact.

688
00:29:48,990 --> 00:29:51,760
(How did it feel
filming at a real tournament?)

689
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:56,550
Wow, it was just right.
It was my childhood dream

690
00:29:56,580 --> 00:29:58,380
to get into the player booth,

691
00:29:58,410 --> 00:30:02,240
sitting in
those actual pro esports chairs.

692
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:05,280
We went to film at BITEC Bangna

693
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:09,410
at the actual venue
where they were holding a tournament.

694
00:30:09,430 --> 00:30:12,610
I mean, wow, the stage and all...

695
00:30:13,430 --> 00:30:15,430
The setup was so realistic.

696
00:30:15,460 --> 00:30:16,930
Well, it was the real thing, actually.

697
00:30:16,950 --> 00:30:19,400
So it made me feel a bit pressured.

698
00:30:19,430 --> 00:30:21,680
It felt inspired.

699
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:24,030
You know, back when I was a kid,

700
00:30:24,150 --> 00:30:28,180
I'd see KritNgi compete.

701
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:33,900
They were so cool,
forming their teams and...

702
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:37,300
There'd be that shot
of them putting on their headsets,

703
00:30:37,710 --> 00:30:41,510
gripping the phones,
playing hard, and then winning.

704
00:30:43,580 --> 00:30:46,040
Yeah, a total childhood dream.

705
00:30:46,890 --> 00:30:51,870
We also got to meet teams
of actual professional gamers

706
00:30:51,890 --> 00:30:54,100
who were champions.

707
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:55,930
They were at the shoot that day.

708
00:30:56,210 --> 00:31:00,620
When I actually met those people
who play games that much,

709
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:04,690
it made me stop and think to myself
during the scenes,

710
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:08,010
"Wait, am I going to
look like a total noob?

711
00:31:08,550 --> 00:31:11,290
Does this look like a noob?"

712
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:14,610
We filmed on the day
of an actual national tournament.

713
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:18,800
We even got to sit in the chairs
before they did.

714
00:31:18,820 --> 00:31:20,730
It's like we got to
break them in for them.

715
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:26,040
And with the crowd,
the lights, the sound,

716
00:31:26,070 --> 00:31:28,730
all the gear they use
for the actual tournament,

717
00:31:28,750 --> 00:31:30,430
and the real pro-player chairs,

718
00:31:30,870 --> 00:31:33,510
it made me so pumped up.
It was exhilarating.

719
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:36,030
At the time,

720
00:31:36,230 --> 00:31:38,620
they also had
these player lounges backstage,

721
00:31:38,770 --> 00:31:40,550
and we got to use one of them.

722
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:44,220
It felt like,
"Whoa, I'm like a real pro player."

723
00:31:45,550 --> 00:31:46,650
It felt very real

724
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,650
since we were at the actual venue.

725
00:31:48,810 --> 00:31:53,710
The audience in the scene
came to watch the actual tournament.

726
00:31:54,230 --> 00:31:55,600
It was real, you know.

727
00:31:55,620 --> 00:31:56,820
And there I was, walking out,

728
00:31:56,850 --> 00:31:59,000
acting like a pro player.

729
00:31:59,220 --> 00:32:01,330
I was pretty pressured, too.

730
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:04,160
My reasons are probably
similar to Gunner's

731
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:05,470
in the sense that...

732
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:09,720
We were stepping into the shoes
of actual pro players.

733
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:13,890
We didn't want
our portrayal of the role

734
00:32:13,910 --> 00:32:18,460
to end up diminishing
what they do in real life.

735
00:32:18,490 --> 00:32:19,860
I just wanted to do the best,

736
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:22,840
so it felt a bit nerve-wracking.

737
00:32:23,870 --> 00:32:27,100
I actually had a chance
with this series once before,

738
00:32:27,850 --> 00:32:30,990
so I went back
to talk to the author again.

739
00:32:31,020 --> 00:32:32,200
And the author...

740
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:34,850
- was very protective of it, like...
- Right.

741
00:32:35,010 --> 00:32:36,180
She'd never sold it to anyone,

742
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:38,470
